mnPrLinkStatLinkUp.name: mnPrLinkStatLinkUp
mnPrLinkStatLinkUp.description: True if the radio link itself is up (passing data in both directions.) Note that this can be true even if there are non-critical errors, or even if one or two radios have failed in a protected link.

mnPrLinkStatReachable.name: mnPrLinkStatReachable
mnPrLinkStatReachable.description: A bitmapped object that reveals which of the radios in the link are 'reachable' from the agent (i.e.: which radios have bidirectional connectivity with the agent). Bits (0=lsb) have the following meaning: 0 (mask 1) = NE primary radio is reachable from agent 1 (mask 2) = FE primary radio is reachable from agent 2 (mask 4) = NE secondary radio is reachable from agent 4 (mask 8) = FE secondary radio is reachable from agent

mnPrLinkStatAccessLevel.name: mnPrLinkStatAccessLevel
mnPrLinkStatAccessLevel.description: Indicates the security access level of the request that was used to retrieve this object. Used by management software to determine what access level it has.

mnPrLinkStatLastErrorText.name: mnPrLinkStatLastErrorText
mnPrLinkStatLastErrorText.description: Error text corresponding to last failure while attempting to complete a user's request to change a configuration or control object. Every radio's agent has its own instance of mnPrLinkStatLastErrorText. Even if the object that was not changed is on another radio, the associated error text is stored on the radio where the requesting agent is. This object will be cleared (set to a null string) to help insure that stale messages are not retrieved.

mnPrLinkStatLocalRadioIndex.name: mnPrLinkStatLocalRadioIndex
mnPrLinkStatLocalRadioIndex.description: The radio index for the radio processing the SNMP request. When accessing an ifEntry, using this value as the ifIndex yields the conceptual row of the inter-radio communication interface for this radio. By convention, specific values of the mnPrLinkStatLocalRadioIndex object are assigned as follows: 1 = NE primary radio 2 = FE primary radio (never returned as local index) 3 = NE secondary radio 4 = FE secondary radio (never returned as local index) The assignment of the mnPrLinkStatLocalRadioIndex value persists across reinitializations of the radio.

mnPrRadStatTable.name: mnPrRadStatTable
mnPrRadStatTable.description: A table containing system status information for each radio in the link.

mnPrRadStatEntry.name: mnPrRadStatEntry
mnPrRadStatEntry.description: A set of system status information for a single radio within the link.

mnRadioIndex.name: mnRadioIndex
mnRadioIndex.description: The radio index. When accessing an ifEntry, using this value as the ifIndex yields the conceptual row of the inter-radio communication interface for this radio. By convention, specific values of the mnRadioIndex object are assigned as follows: 1 = NE primary radio 2 = FE primary radio 3 = NE secondary radio 4 = FE secondary radio The assignment of the mnRadioIndex value persists across reinitializations of the radio.

mnPrRadStatCurSeverity.name: mnPrRadStatCurSeverity
mnPrRadStatCurSeverity.description: The maximum current alarm severity for this radio These are the standard values as per ITU X.733. The first release of the radio firmware supports just cleared, major and minor.

mnPrRadStatLatchSeverity.name: mnPrRadStatLatchSeverity
mnPrRadStatLatchSeverity.description: The maximum alarm severity attained by this radio since latched alarms were last reset. These are the standard values as per ITU X.733. The first release of the radio firmware supports just cleared, major and minor.

mnPrRadStatMinorAlarm.name: mnPrRadStatMinorAlarm
mnPrRadStatMinorAlarm.description: True if there is a minor alarm active this radio.

mnPrRadStatControlOn.name: mnPrRadStatControlOn
mnPrRadStatControlOn.description: True if there is a control (mute, loopback, BERT) on (in the non-default, service-affecting state) in this radio.

mnPrRadStatCurAlarmList.name: mnPrRadStatCurAlarmList
mnPrRadStatCurAlarmList.description: List of radio's currently active alarms. The OCTET STRING is a series of up to 128 16-bit words, each word representing the alarm ID of an active alarm, in ascending order by alarm ID. The string is terminated by a word containing 0. This object allows all the alarms to be retrieved in a single PDU.

mnPrRadStatUptime.name: mnPrRadStatUptime
mnPrRadStatUptime.description: The elapsed time, in seconds, since this radio was last rebooted.

mnPrRadStatLastAlarmChangeTime.name: mnPrRadStatLastAlarmChangeTime
mnPrRadStatLastAlarmChangeTime.description: The time the alarm state of this radio last changed. The time is in centiseconds since agent radio was last rebooted: i.e.: it the value of the agent's SysUptime object at the time of the last change.)

mnPrRadStatLastCCChangeTime.name: mnPrRadStatLastCCChangeTime
mnPrRadStatLastCCChangeTime.description: The time that a configuation or control object of this radio was last changed by the user. The time is in centiseconds since agent radio was last rebooted: i.e.: it the value of the agent's SysUptime object at the time of the last change.)

mnPrRadStatLatchedTimeString.name: mnPrRadStatLatchedTimeString
mnPrRadStatLatchedTimeString.description: The elapsed time since latched alarms were last reset on this radio. This object has the format `000d 00:00:00'.

mnPrRadStatImageBooted.name: mnPrRadStatImageBooted
mnPrRadStatImageBooted.description: This object identifies which firmware image is currently running on this radio.

mnPrRadStatIFBoardType.name: mnPrRadStatIFBoardType
mnPrRadStatIFBoardType.description: Installed IF Board Type defined by its physical filter bandwidths (bandwidths of 2.5, 3.5, 5, 7, 10, 14, 20, 25, and 28 MHz for this radio).

mnPrRadStatPSVoltage.name: mnPrRadStatPSVoltage
mnPrRadStatPSVoltage.description: Power Supply type for this radio.

mnPrRadStatODUFreqBand.name: mnPrRadStatODUFreqBand
mnPrRadStatODUFreqBand.description: ODU Frequency Band (GHz) for this radio.

mnPrRadStatODUSubBand.name: mnPrRadStatODUSubBand
mnPrRadStatODUSubBand.description: ODU sub band for this radio.

mnPrRadStatODUTxHigh.name: mnPrRadStatODUTxHigh
mnPrRadStatODUTxHigh.description: ODU Tx High. True if this radio's ODU is Tx High.

mnPrRadStatMinTxFreq.name: mnPrRadStatMinTxFreq
mnPrRadStatMinTxFreq.description: The minimum allowable transmitter frequency for this radio.

mnPrRadStatMaxTxFreq.name: mnPrRadStatMaxTxFreq
mnPrRadStatMaxTxFreq.description: The maximum allowable transmitter frequency for this radio.

mnPrRadStatMinRxFreq.name: mnPrRadStatMinRxFreq
mnPrRadStatMinRxFreq.description: The minimum allowable receiver frequency for this radio.

mnPrRadStatMaxRxFreq.name: mnPrRadStatMaxRxFreq
mnPrRadStatMaxRxFreq.description: The maximum allowable receiver frequency for this radio.

mnPrRadStatProtType.name: mnPrRadStatProtType
mnPrRadStatProtType.description: The protection type of this radio.

mnPrRadStatProtOtherRadioAlarm.name: mnPrRadStatProtOtherRadioAlarm
mnPrRadStatProtOtherRadioAlarm.description: The radio on the other side of the hot standby shelf has a High-Priority Alarm.

mnPrRadStatProtManualMode.name: mnPrRadStatProtManualMode
mnPrRadStatProtManualMode.description: Either a user has set mnPrIDUConfProtOnlineRequest or the switch on the front of the hot standby shelf has been put into the manual position.

mnPrRadStatMinTxPower.name: mnPrRadStatMinTxPower
mnPrRadStatMinTxPower.description: The maximum allowable transmitter power for this radio.

mnPrRadStatMaxTxPower.name: mnPrRadStatMaxTxPower
mnPrRadStatMaxTxPower.description: The minimum allowable transmitter power for this radio.

mnPrRadStatPerfHistDuration.name: mnPrRadStatPerfHistDuration
mnPrRadStatPerfHistDuration.description: The elapsed time of performance history data that is currently available. This is based on the number of records currently stored and the sample frequency. This object has the format `000 d 00:00:00'.

mnPrRadStatPerfHistMinDuration.name: mnPrRadStatPerfHistMinDuration
mnPrRadStatPerfHistMinDuration.description: The minimum time of performance history data that will be available at any time assuming that performance history collection has been enabled for a sufficient amount of time. This is based on the number of records that can be stored and the sample frequency. This object has the format `000 d 00:00:00'.

mnPrRadStatPerfHistRecords.name: mnPrRadStatPerfHistRecords
mnPrRadStatPerfHistRecords.description: The number of performance history samples that are currently available.

mnPrRadStatPerfHistMinRecords.name: mnPrRadStatPerfHistMinRecords
mnPrRadStatPerfHistMinRecords.description: The minimum number of performance history samples that will be available at any time assuming that performance history collection has been enabled for a sufficient amount of time.

mnPrRadStatPerfHistMaxVarIndex.name: mnPrRadStatPerfHistMaxVarIndex
mnPrRadStatPerfHistMaxVarIndex.description: The maximum number of performance history variables available to be sampled. This cannot exceed 32.

mnPrRadStatTrSpace.name: mnPrRadStatTrSpace
mnPrRadStatTrSpace.description: The transmit/receive spacing in kilohertz for this radio.

mnPrRadStatModulation.name: mnPrRadStatModulation
mnPrRadStatModulation.description: The modulation type used for the current modem configuration.

mnPrRadStatProtToggleMode.name: mnPrRadStatProtToggleMode
mnPrRadStatProtToggleMode.description: Position of the Protection Toggle Switch on the LSM directly connected to this radio. positionAuto(1) allows automatic protection switching. The other two values force all the traffic to go through the either the Primary or the Secondary (AMT-M).

mnPrRadStatSysGainProp.name: mnPrRadStatSysGainProp
mnPrRadStatSysGainProp.description: Proposed system gain in dB. (resulting from the 'Evaluate Configuration' operation). (AMT-M)

mnPrRouteStatTable.name: mnPrRouteStatTable
mnPrRouteStatTable.description: A table containing IP routing information for each radio within the link.

mnPrRouteStatEntry.name: mnPrRouteStatEntry
mnPrRouteStatEntry.description: The IP routing information for a single radio within the link.

mnPrRouteStatDestination.name: mnPrRouteStatDestination
mnPrRouteStatDestination.description: The destination IP address of this route.

mnPrRouteStatMask.name: mnPrRouteStatMask
mnPrRouteStatMask.description: The IP subnet mask of this route.

mnPrRouteStatNextHop.name: mnPrRouteStatNextHop
mnPrRouteStatNextHop.description: The next-hop IP address of this route.

mnPrRouteStatMetric.name: mnPrRouteStatMetric
mnPrRouteStatMetric.description: The routing metric (number of routing hops) for this route.

mnPrRouteStatInterface.name: mnPrRouteStatInterface
mnPrRouteStatInterface.description: The interface that packets egress when using this route.

mnPrRouteStatType.name: mnPrRouteStatType
mnPrRouteStatType.description: The type of route this is. Currently supported strings are: IND - indirect route (route through router) DIR - direct route (no additional routing hops)

mnPrRouteStatHowAdded.name: mnPrRouteStatHowAdded
mnPrRouteStatHowAdded.description: What caused this route to be added. Currently supported strings are: System - route added by operating system Dynamic - route added by dynamic routing protocol Static - route added by static user entry

mnPrCurAlarmTable.name: mnPrCurAlarmTable
mnPrCurAlarmTable.description: A table containing current alarm status information for each radio within the link. This table has a primary index, mnRadioIndex, associated with a radio within the link. This table has a secondary index, mnPrCurAlarmID, associated with a specific alarm.

mnPrCurAlarmEntry.name: mnPrCurAlarmEntry
mnPrCurAlarmEntry.description: A set of information about a single active alarm within the link.

mnPrCurAlarmText.name: mnPrCurAlarmText
mnPrCurAlarmText.description: The textual description of this current alarm.

mnPrLatAlarmTable.name: mnPrLatAlarmTable
mnPrLatAlarmTable.description: A table containing latched (previously active but not currently active) alarm status information for each radio within the link. This table has a primary index, mnPradioIndex, associated with a radio within the link. This table has a secondary index, mnPrLatAlarmID, associated with a specific alarm.

mnPrLatAlarmEntry.name: mnPrLatAlarmEntry
mnPrLatAlarmEntry.description: A set of information about a single latched alarm within the link.

mnPrLatAlarmText.name: mnPrLatAlarmText
mnPrLatAlarmText.description: The textual description of this latched alarm.

mnPrNotifyParameter.name: mnPrNotifyParameter
mnPrNotifyParameter.description: This object provides additional information for a alarm. Values are alarm-specific.

mnPrNotifyRadioIndex.name: mnPrNotifyRadioIndex
mnPrNotifyRadioIndex.description: This object provides the mnRadioIndex value representing the radio experiencing the alarm, relative to the relaying (agent) radio. The trap will have the IP address of the relaying radio, but the RadioIndex will indicate which radio the alarm is associated with.

mnPrNotifyRadioName.name: mnPrNotifyRadioName
mnPrNotifyRadioName.description: This object provides the administratively assigned name of the radio experiencing the alarm. The value of this object is configured via the mnPrSysConfRadioName object.

mnPrNotifyTimeStamp.name: mnPrNotifyTimeStamp
mnPrNotifyTimeStamp.description: The time that the alarm was sent, according to the originating radio's realtime clock.

mnPrFNotificationMajorAlarmSet.name: mnPrFNotificationMajorAlarmSet
mnPrFNotificationMajorAlarmSet.description: A major level Alarm was set (see varbinds for details).

mnPrFNotificationAlarmClear.name: mnPrFNotificationAlarmClear
mnPrFNotificationAlarmClear.description: An Alarm was cleared (see varbinds for details).

mnPrFNotificationMinorAlarmSet.name: mnPrFNotificationMinorAlarmSet
mnPrFNotificationMinorAlarmSet.description: A minor level Alarm was set (see varbinds for details).

mnPrFNotificationInfoAlarmSet.name: mnPrFNotificationInfoAlarmSet
mnPrFNotificationInfoAlarmSet.description: An informational Alarm was set (see varbinds for details).

mnPrNotificationMajorAlarmSet.name: mnPrNotificationMajorAlarmSet
mnPrNotificationMajorAlarmSet.description: A major level Alarm was set (see varbinds for details).

mnPrNotificationAlarmClear.name: mnPrNotificationAlarmClear
mnPrNotificationAlarmClear.description: An Alarm was cleared (see varbinds for details).

mnPrNotificationMinorAlarmSet.name: mnPrNotificationMinorAlarmSet
mnPrNotificationMinorAlarmSet.description: A minor level Alarm was set (see varbinds for details).

mnPrNotificationInfoAlarmSet.name: mnPrNotificationInfoAlarmSet
mnPrNotificationInfoAlarmSet.description: An informational Alarm was set (see varbinds for details).

mnPrPerfBaseTable.name: mnPrPerfBaseTable
mnPrPerfBaseTable.description: A table containing the base performance objects from whose values all other performance statistics and performance history is derived. The objects are gauges and counters, and the counters start counting when the radio is initialized, and are never reset. Virtual 64-bit counters (Display64 DisplayString objects) are used in some circumstances to ensure that no counter can possibly overflow in less than 100 years.

mnPrPerfBaseEntry.name: mnPrPerfBaseEntry
mnPrPerfBaseEntry.description: A set of base performance objects for a single radio or interface.

mnInterfaceIndex.name: mnInterfaceIndex
mnInterfaceIndex.description: Union of the Radio Index and Tributary Index. For indexing tables that can have rows referring to either kind of interface.

mnPrPerfBaseTxPower.name: mnPrPerfBaseTxPower
mnPrPerfBaseTxPower.description: The actual transmit power for this radio in dBm, resulting from user setting or ATPC. -100 is returned if the TxPower is not known. -101 is returned if the Transmitter has failed. -102 is returned if the Transmitter is muted. 0 is returned if the row refers to a tributary.

mnPrPerfBaseRSL.name: mnPrPerfBaseRSL
mnPrPerfBaseRSL.description: The received signal level (RSL) in dBm. 0 is returned if the row refers to a tributary.

mnPrPerfBaseFadeMargin.name: mnPrPerfBaseFadeMargin
mnPrPerfBaseFadeMargin.description: The current fade margin in dBm. 0 is returned if the row refers to a tributary.

mnPrPerfBaseElapsedSecs.name: mnPrPerfBaseElapsedSecs
mnPrPerfBaseElapsedSecs.description: The count of seconds since the radio software initialized (seconds of uptime). May not be reset.

mnPrPerfBaseASs.name: mnPrPerfBaseASs
mnPrPerfBaseASs.description: The count of G.826 Available Seconds observed for the radio or tributary interface in question since the radio software initialized. May not be reset.

mnPrPerfBaseUSs.name: mnPrPerfBaseUSs
mnPrPerfBaseUSs.description: The count of G.826 Unavailable Seconds observed for the radio or tributary interface in question since the radio software initialized. May not be reset.

mnPrPerfBaseESs.name: mnPrPerfBaseESs
mnPrPerfBaseESs.description: The count of G.826 Errored Seconds observed for the radio or tributary interface in question since the radio software initialized. May not be reset.

mnPrPerfBaseSESs.name: mnPrPerfBaseSESs
mnPrPerfBaseSESs.description: The count of G.826 Severely Errored Seconds observed for the radio or tributary interface in question since the radio software initialized. May not be reset.

mnPrPerfBaseTotalBlocks.name: mnPrPerfBaseTotalBlocks
mnPrPerfBaseTotalBlocks.description: The count of G.826 blocks passed by the radio or tributary interface in question since the radio software initialized. 64-bit counter expressed as an ASCII string. May not be reset.

mnPrPerfBaseErrBlocks.name: mnPrPerfBaseErrBlocks
mnPrPerfBaseErrBlocks.description: The count of G.826 errored blocks observed by the radio or tributary interface in question since the radio software initialized. 64-bit counter expressed as an ASCII string. May not be reset.

mnPrPerfBaseBBEs.name: mnPrPerfBaseBBEs
mnPrPerfBaseBBEs.description: The count of G.826 background block errors observed by the radio or tributary interface in question since the radio software initialized. 64-bit counter expressed as an ASCII string. May not be reset.

mnPrPerfSumIntTable.name: mnPrPerfSumIntTable
mnPrPerfSumIntTable.description: A table that summarizes key performance statistics over overlapping intervals leading up to the present: Last Second, Last Minute, Last Hour, Last Day and Last Week. There is a column for each statistic, and a row for each of the five intervals.

mnPrPerfSumIntEntry.name: mnPrPerfSumIntEntry
mnPrPerfSumIntEntry.description: A set of performance statistics for a single radio or interface and for a single summary interval.

mnIntervalIndex.name: mnIntervalIndex
mnIntervalIndex.description: Index enumerating what summary interval is being referred to.

mnPrPerfSumIntESs.name: mnPrPerfSumIntESs
mnPrPerfSumIntESs.description: Count of errored seconds for the radio or interface in question, over the summary interval in question.

mnPrPerfSumIntSESs.name: mnPrPerfSumIntSESs
mnPrPerfSumIntSESs.description: Count of severely errored seconds for the radio or interface in question, over the summary interval in question.

mnPrPerfSumIntBER.name: mnPrPerfSumIntBER
mnPrPerfSumIntBER.description: Bit Error Rate for the radio or interface in question, over the summary interval in question. Bit Error Rate is expressed as a string in the format n.nnE-mm.

mnPrPerfSumIntElapsedSecs.name: mnPrPerfSumIntElapsedSecs
mnPrPerfSumIntElapsedSecs.description: Count of elapsed seconds for the radio or interface in question, over the summary interval in question.

mnPrPerfSumIntASs.name: mnPrPerfSumIntASs
mnPrPerfSumIntASs.description: Count of available seconds for the radio or interface in question, over the summary interval in question.

mnPrPerfCustIntTable.name: mnPrPerfCustIntTable
mnPrPerfCustIntTable.description: A table containing performance statistics for the 'Custom Interval' from the user's last reset of the custom interval to the present, with one row for each radio or interface in the link. The system command resetCustomPerformanceInterval resets all these statistics and thus starts a new custom interval.

mnPrPerfCustIntEntry.name: mnPrPerfCustIntEntry
mnPrPerfCustIntEntry.description: A set of performance statistics pertaining to the custom interval for a single radio or interface.

mnPrPerfCustIntTxPowerAvg.name: mnPrPerfCustIntTxPowerAvg
mnPrPerfCustIntTxPowerAvg.description: The average transmit power for this radio in dBm, over the custom interval. Format: '-xx.x'. '' is returned if the row refers to a tributary.

mnPrPerfCustIntTxPowerMax.name: mnPrPerfCustIntTxPowerMax
mnPrPerfCustIntTxPowerMax.description: The maximum transmit power for this radio in dBm, over the custom interval. 0 is returned if the row refers to a tributary.

mnPrPerfCustIntTxPowerMin.name: mnPrPerfCustIntTxPowerMin
mnPrPerfCustIntTxPowerMin.description: The minimum transmit power for this radio in dBm, over the custom interval. 0 is returned if the row refers to a tributary.

mnPrPerfCustIntRSLAvg.name: mnPrPerfCustIntRSLAvg
mnPrPerfCustIntRSLAvg.description: The average RSL for this radio in dBm, over the custom interval. Format: '-xx.x'. '' is returned if the row refers to a tributary.

mnPrPerfCustIntRSLMax.name: mnPrPerfCustIntRSLMax
mnPrPerfCustIntRSLMax.description: The maximum RSL for this radio in dBm, over the custom interval. 0 is returned if the row refers to a tributary.

mnPrPerfCustIntRSLMin.name: mnPrPerfCustIntRSLMin
mnPrPerfCustIntRSLMin.description: The minimum RSL for this radio in dBm, over the custom interval. 0 is returned if the row refers to a tributary.

mnPrPerfCustIntElapsedSecs.name: mnPrPerfCustIntElapsedSecs
mnPrPerfCustIntElapsedSecs.description: The count of seconds since the custom interval was reset.

mnPrPerfCustIntASs.name: mnPrPerfCustIntASs
mnPrPerfCustIntASs.description: The count of G.826 Available Seconds observed for the radio or tributary interface in question since the custom interval was reset.

mnPrPerfCustIntUSs.name: mnPrPerfCustIntUSs
mnPrPerfCustIntUSs.description: The count of G.826 Unavailable Seconds observed for the radio or tributary interface in question since the custom interval was reset.

mnPrPerfCustIntESs.name: mnPrPerfCustIntESs
mnPrPerfCustIntESs.description: The count of G.826 Errored Seconds observed for the radio or tributary interface in question since the custom interval was reset.

mnPrPerfCustIntSESs.name: mnPrPerfCustIntSESs
mnPrPerfCustIntSESs.description: The count of G.826 Severely Errored Seconds observed for the radio or tributary interface in question since the custom interval was reset.

mnPrPerfCustIntTotalBlocks.name: mnPrPerfCustIntTotalBlocks
mnPrPerfCustIntTotalBlocks.description: The count of G.826 blocks passed by the radio or tributary interface in question since the custom interval was reset. 64-bit counter expressed as an ASCII string.

mnPrPerfCustIntErrBlocks.name: mnPrPerfCustIntErrBlocks
mnPrPerfCustIntErrBlocks.description: The count of G.826 errored blocks observed by the radio or tributary interface in question since the custom interval was reset. 64-bit counter expressed as an ASCII string.

mnPrPerfCustIntBBEs.name: mnPrPerfCustIntBBEs
mnPrPerfCustIntBBEs.description: The count of G.826 background block errors observed by the radio or tributary interface in question since the custom interval was reset. 64-bit counter expressed as an ASCII string.

mnPrPerfCustIntESRatio.name: mnPrPerfCustIntESRatio
mnPrPerfCustIntESRatio.description: Standard G.826 ratio of Errored Seconds / Available Seconds for the radio or interface in question, over the Custom interval. Expressed as a string in the format 'x.xxxxxxxx'.

mnPrPerfCustIntSESRatio.name: mnPrPerfCustIntSESRatio
mnPrPerfCustIntSESRatio.description: Standard G.826 ratio of Severely Errored Seconds / Available Seconds for the radio or interface in question, over the Custom interval. Expressed as a string in the format 'x.xxxxxxxx'.

mnPrPerfCustIntBER.name: mnPrPerfCustIntBER
mnPrPerfCustIntBER.description: Bit Error Rate for the radio or interface in question, over the Custom interval. Bit Error Rate is expressed as a string in the format n.nnE-mm.

mnPrPerfCustIntBBER.name: mnPrPerfCustIntBBER
mnPrPerfCustIntBBER.description: Background Bit Error Rate for the radio or interface in question, over the Custom interval. Bit Error Rate is expressed as a string in the format n.nnE-mm. This is the same as the normal BER, but using only background bit errors (bit errors in seconds that are not severely errored), not all bit errors.

mnPrPerfHistTable.name: mnPrPerfHistTable
mnPrPerfHistTable.description: A table that contains performance statistics samples taken over a period of time leading up to the present. There is a column for each statistic, and a row for each sample available from the history collection.

mnPrPerfHistEntry.name: mnPrPerfHistEntry
mnPrPerfHistEntry.description: A set of performance statistics pertaining to a single radio or interface during a previous period of time.

mnPrPerfHistTimestamp.name: mnPrPerfHistTimestamp
mnPrPerfHistTimestamp.description: The real-time clock value at the time this sample was taken. The 8-OCTET varient (no time zone information) is used, and deci-seconds is always 0: field octets contents range _____ ______ ________ _____ 1 1-2 year 0..65536 (in network byte order) 2 3 month 1..12 3 4 day 1..31 4 5 hour 0..23 5 6 minutes 0..59 6 7 seconds 0..60 (use 60 for leap-second) 7 8 deci-seconds 0..9

mnPrPerfHistElapsedSecs.name: mnPrPerfHistElapsedSecs
mnPrPerfHistElapsedSecs.description: The count of seconds since the previous sample was taken.

mnPrPerfHistDowntime.name: mnPrPerfHistDowntime
mnPrPerfHistDowntime.description: The count of seconds of downtime for the radio since the previous sample was taken.

mnPrPerfHistASs.name: mnPrPerfHistASs
mnPrPerfHistASs.description: The count of G.826 Available Seconds observed for the radio or tributary interface in question since the previous sample was taken.

mnPrPerfHistUSs.name: mnPrPerfHistUSs
mnPrPerfHistUSs.description: The count of G.826 Unavailable Seconds observed for the radio or tributary interface in question since the previous sample was taken.

mnPrPerfHistESs.name: mnPrPerfHistESs
mnPrPerfHistESs.description: The count of G.826 Errored Seconds observed for the radio or tributary interface in question since the previous sample was taken.

mnPrPerfHistSESs.name: mnPrPerfHistSESs
mnPrPerfHistSESs.description: The count of G.826 Severely Errored Seconds observed for the radio or tributary interface in question since the previous sample was taken.

mnPrPerfHistTotalBlocks.name: mnPrPerfHistTotalBlocks
mnPrPerfHistTotalBlocks.description: The count of G.826 blocks passed by the radio or tributary interface in question since the previous sample was taken. 64-bit counter expressed as an ASCII string.

mnPrPerfHistErrBlocks.name: mnPrPerfHistErrBlocks
mnPrPerfHistErrBlocks.description: The count of G.826 errored blocks observed by the radio or tributary interface in question since the previous sample was taken. 64-bit counter expressed as an ASCII string.

mnPrPerfHistErrBackBlocks.name: mnPrPerfHistErrBackBlocks
mnPrPerfHistErrBackBlocks.description: The count of G.826 background block errors observed by the radio or tributary interface in question since the previous sample was taken. 64-bit counter expressed as an ASCII string.

mnPrPerfHistTotalBytes.name: mnPrPerfHistTotalBytes
mnPrPerfHistTotalBytes.description: The count of G.826 bytes passed by the radio or tributary interface in question since the previous sample was taken. 64-bit counter expressed as an ASCII string.

mnPrPerfHistErrBytes.name: mnPrPerfHistErrBytes
mnPrPerfHistErrBytes.description: The count of G.826 errored bytes observed by the radio or tributary interface in question since the previous sample was taken. 64-bit counter expressed as an ASCII string.

mnPrPerfHistTotalBackBytes.name: mnPrPerfHistTotalBackBytes
mnPrPerfHistTotalBackBytes.description: The count of G.826 background bytes passed by the radio or tributary interface in question since the previous sample was taken. 64-bit counter expressed as an ASCII string.

mnPrPerfHistErrBackBytes.name: mnPrPerfHistErrBackBytes
mnPrPerfHistErrBackBytes.description: The count of G.826 errored background bytes observed by the radio or tributary interface in question since the previous sample was taken. 64-bit counter expressed as an ASCII string.

mnPrPerfHistESRatio.name: mnPrPerfHistESRatio
mnPrPerfHistESRatio.description: Standard G.826 ratio of Errored Seconds / Available Seconds for the radio or interface in question, over the previous sample period. Expressed as a string in the format 'n.nnE-mm'.

mnPrPerfHistSESRatio.name: mnPrPerfHistSESRatio
mnPrPerfHistSESRatio.description: Standard G.826 ratio of Severely Errored Seconds / Available Seconds for the radio or interface in question, over the previous sample period. Expressed as a string in the format 'n.nnE-mm'.

mnPrPerfHistBER.name: mnPrPerfHistBER
mnPrPerfHistBER.description: Bit Error Rate for the radio or interface in question, over the previous sample period. Bit Error Rate is expressed as a string in the format n.nnE-mm.

mnPrPerfHistBBER.name: mnPrPerfHistBBER
mnPrPerfHistBBER.description: Background Bit Error Rate for the radio or interface in question, over the previous sample period. Bit Error Rate is expressed as a string in the format n.nnE-mm. This is the same as the normal BER, but using only background bit errors (bit errors in seconds that are not severely errored), not all bit errors.

mnPrPerfHistTxPower.name: mnPrPerfHistTxPower
mnPrPerfHistTxPower.description: The current transmit power for this radio in dBm, when this sample was taken. 0 is returned if the row refers to a tributary.

mnPrPerfHistTxPowerMin.name: mnPrPerfHistTxPowerMin
mnPrPerfHistTxPowerMin.description: The minimum transmit power for this radio in dBm, over the previous sample period. 0 is returned if the row refers to a tributary.

mnPrPerfHistTxPowerMax.name: mnPrPerfHistTxPowerMax
mnPrPerfHistTxPowerMax.description: The maximum transmit power for this radio in dBm, over the previous sample period. 0 is returned if the row refers to a tributary.

mnPrPerfHistTxPowerAvg.name: mnPrPerfHistTxPowerAvg
mnPrPerfHistTxPowerAvg.description: The average transmit power for this radio in dBm, over the previous sample period. Format: '-xx.x'. '' is returned if the row refers to a tributary.

mnPrPerfHistRSL.name: mnPrPerfHistRSL
mnPrPerfHistRSL.description: The RSL for this radio in dBm, when this sample was taken. 0 is returned if the row refers to a tributary.

mnPrPerfHistRSLMin.name: mnPrPerfHistRSLMin
mnPrPerfHistRSLMin.description: The minimum RSL for this radio in dBm, over the previous sample period. 0 is returned if the row refers to a tributary.

mnPrPerfHistRSLMax.name: mnPrPerfHistRSLMax
mnPrPerfHistRSLMax.description: The maximum RSL for this radio in dBm, over the previous sample period. 0 is returned if the row refers to a tributary.

mnPrPerfHistRSLAvg.name: mnPrPerfHistRSLAvg
mnPrPerfHistRSLAvg.description: The average RSL for this radio in dBm, over the previous sample. Format: '-xx.x'. '' is returned if the row refers to a tributary.

mnPrPerfHistCsvHdrTable.name: mnPrPerfHistCsvHdrTable
mnPrPerfHistCsvHdrTable.description: A table that contains performance statistics variable names currently selected for sampling. This table contains a comma separated values string containing all sampled performance variable names in a single row.

mnPrPerfHistCsvHdrEntry.name: mnPrPerfHistCsvHdrEntry
mnPrPerfHistCsvHdrEntry.description: The column header names for a set of performance statistics pertaining to a single radio or interface during a previous period of time in CSV (comma separated values) format.

mnPrPerfHistCsvHdr.name: mnPrPerfHistCsvHdr
mnPrPerfHistCsvHdr.description: The column headers for the set of performance statistics selected for history collection in CSV (comma separated values) format.

mnPrPerfHistCsvDataTable.name: mnPrPerfHistCsvDataTable
mnPrPerfHistCsvDataTable.description: A table that contains performance statistics samples taken over a period of time leading up to the present. This table contains a comma separated values string containing all sampled performance variable values in a row for each sample available from the history collection.

mnPrPerfHistCsvDataEntry.name: mnPrPerfHistCsvDataEntry
mnPrPerfHistCsvDataEntry.description: A set of performance statistics pertaining to a single radio or interface during a previous period of time in CSV (comma separated values) format.

mnPrPerfHistCsvData.name: mnPrPerfHistCsvData
mnPrPerfHistCsvData.description: A set of performance statistics pertaining to a single radio or interface during a previous period of time in CSV (comma separated values) format.

mnPrRadCtlTable.name: mnPrRadCtlTable
mnPrRadCtlTable.description: A table containing objects used to control the radio and monitor the effects of that control. These controls are generally for diagnostic purposes, and are not saved in flash, so they do not persist after the radio re-initializes.

mnPrRadCtlEntry.name: mnPrRadCtlEntry
mnPrRadCtlEntry.description: Control objects for one radio in the link.

mnPrRadCtlDigAggLoopback.name: mnPrRadCtlDigAggLoopback
mnPrRadCtlDigAggLoopback.description: If set to 'True', enables digital aggregate loopback (loops IDU's entire aggregate digital output signal back into IDU.)

mnPrRadCtlBERTTxPattern.name: mnPrRadCtlBERTTxPattern
mnPrRadCtlBERTTxPattern.description: Enables or disables IDU's Internal Aggregate BER Tester (BERT). Power-up default is 'disableBERT(1)'. When BERT is enabled, all the associated read-only variables are set to thier initial values (0). When the BERT is disabled, the variables are frozen.

mnPrRadCtlBERTTimeString.name: mnPrRadCtlBERTTimeString
mnPrRadCtlBERTTimeString.description: The elapsed time since the BERT was enabled. Format: `000d 00:00:00'.

mnPrRadCtlBERTTotal.name: mnPrRadCtlBERTTotal
mnPrRadCtlBERTTotal.description: The total count of bits received by the BERT receiver since the BERT was enabled. Initial value is '0'.

mnPrRadCtlBERTErrors.name: mnPrRadCtlBERTErrors
mnPrRadCtlBERTErrors.description: The total count of ERRORRED bits received by the BERT receiver since the BERT was enabled. Initial value is '0'.

mnPrRadCtlBERTBER.name: mnPrRadCtlBERTBER
mnPrRadCtlBERTBER.description: Bit Error Rate seen by the BERT receiver for the entire period from when the BERT was enabled to the present. Format n.nnnnnnE-mm. Initial value is '0.000000E-00'.

mnPrRadCtrDigAggLoopTime.name: mnPrRadCtrDigAggLoopTime
mnPrRadCtrDigAggLoopTime.description: This is the time in seconds that the aggregate loopback will stay on. A value of 0 indicates that the loopback will stay on forever. The maximum value is 3600 (one hour).

mnPrRadCtlODUMute.name: mnPrRadCtlODUMute
mnPrRadCtlODUMute.description: If TRUE, ODU is muted. Note that this is the user initiated mute state which is saved in flash, so mute state persists across reboots. Also note that mnPrODUConfMute can also cause the ODU to be muted based on the online state of the IDU. UserMute ProtectionMute mnPrRadCtlODUMute mnPrODUConfMute EM Mute State - - False False Online - X False True Standby X - True True Muted X X True True Muted

mnPrRadCtlODUMuteTime.name: mnPrRadCtlODUMuteTime
mnPrRadCtlODUMuteTime.description: This is the time in seconds that the ODU will remain muted. A value of 0 indicates that the mute will stay on forever. The maximum value is 3600 (one hour).

mnPrLIMCtlTable.name: mnPrLIMCtlTable
mnPrLIMCtlTable.description: A table containing objects used to control the LIM and monitor the effects of that control. These controls are generally for diagnostic purposes, and are not saved in flash, so they do not persist after the radio re-initializes.

mnPrLIMCtlEntry.name: mnPrLIMCtlEntry
mnPrLIMCtlEntry.description: Control objects for one radio in the link.

mnPrLIMCtlBERTTrib.name: mnPrLIMCtlBERTTrib
mnPrLIMCtlBERTTrib.description: Specifies what Tributary within the LIM that the Internal LIM BER Tester (BERT) will operate on.

mnPrLIMCtlBERTTxPattern.name: mnPrLIMCtlBERTTxPattern
mnPrLIMCtlBERTTxPattern.description: Enables or disables LIM's Internal Tributary BER Tester (BERT). Power-up default is 'disableBERT(1)'. When BERT is enabled, all the associated read-only variables are set to thier initial values (0). When the BERT is disabled, the variables are frozen.

mnPrLIMCtlBERTTimeString.name: mnPrLIMCtlBERTTimeString
mnPrLIMCtlBERTTimeString.description: The elapsed time since the BERT was enabled. Format: `000d 00:00:00'.

mnPrLIMCtlBERTTotal.name: mnPrLIMCtlBERTTotal
mnPrLIMCtlBERTTotal.description: The total count of bits received by the BERT receiver since the BERT was enabled. Initial value is '0'.

mnPrLIMCtlBERTErrors.name: mnPrLIMCtlBERTErrors
mnPrLIMCtlBERTErrors.description: The total count of ERRORRED bits received by the BERT receiver since the BERT was enabled. Initial value is '0'.

mnPrLIMCtlBERTBER.name: mnPrLIMCtlBERTBER
mnPrLIMCtlBERTBER.description: Bit Error Rate seen by the BERT receiver for the entire period from when the BERT was enabled to the present. Format n.nnnnnnE-mm. Initial value is '0.000000E-00'.

mnPrTribCtlTable.name: mnPrTribCtlTable
mnPrTribCtlTable.description: A table containing objects used to control the tributaries. These controls are generally for diagnostic purposes, and are not saved in flash, so they do not persist after the radio re-initializes.

mnPrTribCtlEntry.name: mnPrTribCtlEntry
mnPrTribCtlEntry.description: Control objects for one tributary in the link.

mnTribIndex.name: mnTribIndex
mnTribIndex.description: xyzz, where x=radio index, y=LIM #, and zz=Tributary number on LIM 1101 2101 etc. If Tributary number is 00, then this value is for the LIM itself.

mnPrTribCtlLocalLoopback.name: mnPrTribCtlLocalLoopback
mnPrTribCtlLocalLoopback.description: If set to 'True', enables tributary local loopback (loops incoming tributary signal back out to customer equipment.)

mnPrTribCtlRemoteLoopback.name: mnPrTribCtlRemoteLoopback
mnPrTribCtlRemoteLoopback.description: If set to 'True', enables tributary remote loopback (loops outgoing tributary signal back into tributary.)

mnPrInventTable.name: mnPrInventTable
mnPrInventTable.description: A table containing inventory information and service state about each component within this link. The service state is provided for components that exist within the product, but are disabled for some reason, usually due to feature license restrictions.

mnPrInventCompIndex.name: mnPrInventCompIndex
mnPrInventCompIndex.description: Component Index 10 = ODU 11 = ODU Firmware 20 = IDU 21 = IDU Firmware 22 = IF Board 23 = IDU Power Supply 30 = LIMA 40 = LIMB 50 = Image 1 Firmware 51 = Image 2 Firmware 60 = TX FPGA Firmware 61 = RX FPGA Firmware 62 = E1 FPGA Firmware etc.

mnPrInventModPartText.name: mnPrInventModPartText
mnPrInventModPartText.description: The text form of the Model ID / Part Number (if any).

mnPrInventCheckSumText.name: mnPrInventCheckSumText
mnPrInventCheckSumText.description: The text form of the code checksum (if any).

mnPrInventVersionText.name: mnPrInventVersionText
mnPrInventVersionText.description: The text form of the Version (if any).

mnPrInventSerialText.name: mnPrInventSerialText
mnPrInventSerialText.description: The text form of the Serial Number (if any).

mnPrInventCompStatus.name: mnPrInventCompStatus
mnPrInventCompStatus.description: The service state of the component.

mnPrInventCompType.name: mnPrInventCompType
mnPrInventCompType.description: Provides more information about a component. For example in LIM rows, this column contains the LIM hardware type code.

mnPrODUConfTable.name: mnPrODUConfTable
mnPrODUConfTable.description: A table containing configuration parameters for the ODUs in the link

mnPrODUConfEntry.name: mnPrODUConfEntry
mnPrODUConfEntry.description: A set of configuration parameters for a single ODU within the link.

mnPrODUConfTxPower.name: mnPrODUConfTxPower
mnPrODUConfTxPower.description: Tx Power, in dBm, for the transmitter of this radio (when TxPower is controlled manually, not by ATPC).

mnPrODUConfATPCEnable.name: mnPrODUConfATPCEnable
mnPrODUConfATPCEnable.description: This object provides a means to administratively enable or disable the ATPC (Automatic Power Control) function.

mnPrODUConfATPCTargetRSL.name: mnPrODUConfATPCTargetRSL
mnPrODUConfATPCTargetRSL.description: The desired received signal level (RSL) in dBm. The value contained in this object is used by the ATPC (Automatic Power Control) function to obtain the desired RSL on the remote side of the link.

mnPrODUConfMute.name: mnPrODUConfMute
mnPrODUConfMute.description: If TRUE, ODU is muted as a hot standby. Note that this is NOT saved in flash, but follows the online state of the IDU. For user initiated ODU mute refer to mnPrRadCtlODUMute.

mnPrIDUConfTable.name: mnPrIDUConfTable
mnPrIDUConfTable.description: A table containing configuration parameters for the IDUs in the link

mnPrIDUConfEntry.name: mnPrIDUConfEntry
mnPrIDUConfEntry.description: A set of configuration parameters for a single IDU within the link.

mnPrIDUConfProtMode.name: mnPrIDUConfProtMode
mnPrIDUConfProtMode.description: This object provides a means to configure the protection mode for this radio.

mnPrIDUConfProtOnlineRequest.name: mnPrIDUConfProtOnlineRequest
mnPrIDUConfProtOnlineRequest.description: This object provides a means to configure the online state of the IDU. When set to True, will request that the hot standby shelf switch to make this IDU the online IDU, regardless of alarm conditions.

mnPrIDUConfOrderwireCode.name: mnPrIDUConfOrderwireCode
mnPrIDUConfOrderwireCode.description: This object provides a means to configure the DTMF dialing code for this IDU.

mnPrIDUConfOrderwireMode.name: mnPrIDUConfOrderwireMode
mnPrIDUConfOrderwireMode.description: This object provides a means to configure the orderwire as a Voice channel or a 64 Kbps Data channel.

mnPrIDUConfAUX1Rate.name: mnPrIDUConfAUX1Rate
mnPrIDUConfAUX1Rate.description: This object provides a means to configure the Auxilary channel 1 as 9600 or 19200 baud.

mnPrIDUConfAUX2Rate.name: mnPrIDUConfAUX2Rate
mnPrIDUConfAUX2Rate.description: This object provides a means to configure the Auxilary channel 2 as 9600 or 19200 baud.

mnPrIDUConfCraftBaud.name: mnPrIDUConfCraftBaud
mnPrIDUConfCraftBaud.description: This object provides a means to configure the craft port baud rate.

mnPrIDUConfProposedCapacity.name: mnPrIDUConfProposedCapacity
mnPrIDUConfProposedCapacity.description: This object shows the total LIM capacity for the proposed LIM types. It acts as the maximum value for mnPrIDUConfAllocateLimA.

mnPrIDUConfAllocateLimA.name: mnPrIDUConfAllocateLimA
mnPrIDUConfAllocateLimA.description: This object provides a means to configure the data rate (in compressed Megabits/second) for LIM A. This object only has meaning when both LIMs are configured as 100 BaseT.

mnPrIDUConfProtTwinAddress.name: mnPrIDUConfProtTwinAddress
mnPrIDUConfProtTwinAddress.description: This object configures the IPv4 address of the twin IDU processor used in hot standby configurations.

mnPrIDUConfIFBandwidthProposed.name: mnPrIDUConfIFBandwidthProposed
mnPrIDUConfIFBandwidthProposed.description: This is a control object (not saved in flash) that allows the user to specify a new value for the Configured IF Bandwidth. Once the proposed type instances for each LIM and the proposed IF bandwidth are set correctly, the reconfigureModem system command checks the proposed configuration settings, and, if they are a legal combination, copies them into the Configured LIM (mnPrLIMConfTypeConf) and Configured IF Bandwidth (mnPrIDUConfIFBandwidthConf) object instances.

mnPrIDUConfIFBandwidthConf.name: mnPrIDUConfIFBandwidthConf
mnPrIDUConfIFBandwidthConf.description: The Configured IF Bandwidth. This is saved in flash. It is set only by the reconfigureModem system command, which, if the proposed combination of LIM types and IF Bandwidth is legal, copies the associated Proposed IF Bandwidth object into this object.

mnPrIDUConfNmsPortSpeed.name: mnPrIDUConfNmsPortSpeed
mnPrIDUConfNmsPortSpeed.description: This object provides a means to configure the LAN speed settings for the NMS ports. It allows the user to enable auto-negotiation or set the speed and duplex settings to a fixed value. (Note: this object is used by AMT-L. AMT-M uses mnPrAuxEthConfTable.)

mnPrIDUConfNmsPortMode.name: mnPrIDUConfNmsPortMode
mnPrIDUConfNmsPortMode.description: This object provides a means to configure the NMS management channel to the far-end. A value of mgmtOutOfBand in this object will configure the hardware such that the NMS and payload ethernet data is isolated from each other. A value of mgmtInBand will bridge the NMS ports to the built-in ethernet payload ports.

mnPrIDUConfCapacityConf.name: mnPrIDUConfCapacityConf
mnPrIDUConfCapacityConf.description: Current total configured capacity in Mb/s. (AMT-M)

mnPrIDUConfCapacityProp.name: mnPrIDUConfCapacityProp
mnPrIDUConfCapacityProp.description: Proposed total configured capacity in Mb/s. (AMT-M)

mnPrIDUConfIntEthStatusInst.name: mnPrIDUConfIntEthStatusInst
mnPrIDUConfIntEthStatusInst.description: Current license status of Integrated Ethernet. (AMT-M)

mnPrIDUConfIntEthStatusConf.name: mnPrIDUConfIntEthStatusConf
mnPrIDUConfIntEthStatusConf.description: Current configured status of Integrated Ethernet. (AMT-M)

mnPrIDUConfIntEthCapacityInst.name: mnPrIDUConfIntEthCapacityInst
mnPrIDUConfIntEthCapacityInst.description: Maximum possible capacity of Integrated Ethernet. (AMT-M)

mnPrLIMConfTable.name: mnPrLIMConfTable
mnPrLIMConfTable.description: A table containing configuration information about each LIM within this link.

mnPrLIMConfEntry.name: mnPrLIMConfEntry
mnPrLIMConfEntry.description: A set of configuration information about a single LIM within this link.

mnPrLIMConfTypeInstalled.name: mnPrLIMConfTypeInstalled
mnPrLIMConfTypeInstalled.description: This is a status object that states what kind of LIM is actually physically installed in the associated LIM slot.

mnPrLIMConfTypeProposed.name: mnPrLIMConfTypeProposed
mnPrLIMConfTypeProposed.description: This is a control object (not saved in flash) that allows the user to specify a new value for the Configured LIM type. Once the instances for each LIM are set correctly, the reconfigureModem system command checks the two instances, and, if they are a legal combination, copies them into the Configured LIM (mnPrLIMConfTypeConf) object instances.

mnPrLIMConfTypeConf.name: mnPrLIMConfTypeConf
mnPrLIMConfTypeConf.description: The Configured LIM type. This is saved in flash. It is set only by the reconfigureLIMs system command, which if the proposed combination is legal, copies the associated Proposed LIM Configuration object into this object.

mnPrLIMConfCapacity.name: mnPrLIMConfCapacity
mnPrLIMConfCapacity.description: This object shows the capacity of the associated LIM in Mbits/sec.

mnPrLIMConfCapacityInst.name: mnPrLIMConfCapacityInst
mnPrLIMConfCapacityInst.description: Maximum possible capacity of the LIM. (AMT-M)

mnPrLIMConfCapacityConf.name: mnPrLIMConfCapacityConf
mnPrLIMConfCapacityConf.description: Currently configured capacity of the LIM. Same as mnPrLIMConfCapacityConf, but 32 bits (not limited to (0..255)). (AMT-M)

mnPrLIMConfCapacityProp.name: mnPrLIMConfCapacityProp
mnPrLIMConfCapacityProp.description: Currently proposed capacity of the LIM. Replaces mnPrIduConfAllocLimA (except that it is 32 bits and has instances for both LIMs.) (AMT-M)

mnPrTribConfTable.name: mnPrTribConfTable
mnPrTribConfTable.description: A table containing configuration information about each tributary within this link.

mnPrTribConfEntry.name: mnPrTribConfEntry
mnPrTribConfEntry.description: A set of configuration information about a single tributary within this link.

mnPrTribConfAdminEquipped.name: mnPrTribConfAdminEquipped
mnPrTribConfAdminEquipped.description: This object provides a means to administratively configure the provisioned equipment state of this tributary.

mnPrSysConfTable.name: mnPrSysConfTable
mnPrSysConfTable.description: A table containing system configuration information for each radio within the link.

mnPrSysConfEntry.name: mnPrSysConfEntry
mnPrSysConfEntry.description: A set of system configuration information for a single radio within the link.

mnPrSysConfRadioName.name: mnPrSysConfRadioName
mnPrSysConfRadioName.description: The administratively assigned name of the radio. The value contained in this object is also reported by the mnPrNotifyRadioName object, and by the MIB-II System Group's SysName objext.

mnPrSysConfLocation.name: mnPrSysConfLocation
mnPrSysConfLocation.description: The administratively assigned physical location of the radio. The value contained in this object is also reported by the MIB-II System Group's SysLocation objext.

mnPrSysConfContact.name: mnPrSysConfContact
mnPrSysConfContact.description: The administratively assigned name and contact information of the designated responsible person for this radio. An example: `G. Marconi +1 800 555-1212, gmarconi@microwavenetworks.com' The value contained in this object is also reported by the MIB-II System Group's SysContact objext.

mnPrSysConfDateAndTime.name: mnPrSysConfDateAndTime
mnPrSysConfDateAndTime.description: Provides a means to set and read the radio's real-time clock. The 8-OCTET varient (no time zone information) is used, and deci-seconds is ignored on write and 0 on read: field octets contents range _____ ______ ________ _____ 1 1-2 year 0..65536 (in network byte order) 2 3 month 1..12 3 4 day 1..31 4 5 hour 0..23 5 6 minutes 0..59 6 7 seconds 0..60 (use 60 for leap-second) 7 8 deci-seconds 0..9

mnPrSysConfLicenseKey.name: mnPrSysConfLicenseKey
mnPrSysConfLicenseKey.description: The upgradeable license key for this radio which unlocks enhanced features.

mnPrSysConfThroughPut.name: mnPrSysConfThroughPut
mnPrSysConfThroughPut.description: This object reports the maximum throughput in mega-bits per second that is licensed for this radio.

mnPrSysConfTimeZone.name: mnPrSysConfTimeZone
mnPrSysConfTimeZone.description: Offset in hours and minutes between the Universal Coordinated Time (UTC) that SNTP uses and the standard local time that the radio will display.Example: +05:30 (5 hours, 30 minutes west of UTC). Leading '+' and zeros are assumed, as is minutes=0, so '5' == '+05:00'.

mnPrSysConfDaylightSavings.name: mnPrSysConfDaylightSavings
mnPrSysConfDaylightSavings.description: Daylight Savings time is in effect: local time will be calculated by adding the timezone offset plus one hour to the UTC time that SNTP supplies.

mnPrUserConfTable.name: mnPrUserConfTable
mnPrUserConfTable.description: List of users for this radio.

mnPrUserConfEntry.name: mnPrUserConfEntry
mnPrUserConfEntry.description: Information about one user of this radio.

mnPrUserConfIndex.name: mnPrUserConfIndex
mnPrUserConfIndex.description: The index of the user database that contains this row

mnPrUserConfPasswordSet.name: mnPrUserConfPasswordSet
mnPrUserConfPasswordSet.description: The user's password. Returns '***' on read, or null string if the password is not set

mnPrAlarmConfTable.name: mnPrAlarmConfTable
mnPrAlarmConfTable.description: A table containing alarm configuration information for each radio within the link.

mnPrAlarmConfEntry.name: mnPrAlarmConfEntry
mnPrAlarmConfEntry.description: A set of alarm configuration information for a single alarm on a single radio within the link.

mnAlarmIndex.name: mnAlarmIndex
mnAlarmIndex.description: This object identifies the alarm. The index is the same number that is sent in the current alarm list.

mnPrAlarmConfName.name: mnPrAlarmConfName
mnPrAlarmConfName.description: This is the full name of the alarm.

mnPrAlarmConfUserName.name: mnPrAlarmConfUserName
mnPrAlarmConfUserName.description: Portion of the alarm name that may be modified by the user. Only valid for external and relay alarms.

mnPrAlarmConfAbrev.name: mnPrAlarmConfAbrev
mnPrAlarmConfAbrev.description: Abbreviated alarm name for making smaller labels.

mnPrAlarmConfMap.name: mnPrAlarmConfMap
mnPrAlarmConfMap.description: This bit-maps the alarm to certain relays / actions. For example: Bit 0: near-end Relay 1 Bit 1: near-end Relay 2 Bit 2: near-end Relay 3 Bit 3: near-end Relay 4 Bit 4: reserved Bit 5: far-end Relay 1 Bit 6: far-end Relay 2 Bit 7: far-end Relay 3 Bit 8: far-end Relay 4 Bit 9: reserved Bit 10: major alarm Bit 11: minor alarm Bit 12: high priority alarm Bit 13: low priority alarm Bit 14 - 31: reserved

mnPrAlarmConfCircuitType.name: mnPrAlarmConfCircuitType
mnPrAlarmConfCircuitType.description: This specifies if associated external input or relay is normally open or normally closed in alarm condition. 99 - Not Applicable 1 - Normally Open (active high) 2 - Normally Closed (active low)

mnPrAlarmConfThreshold.name: mnPrAlarmConfThreshold
mnPrAlarmConfThreshold.description: For alarms that allow settable thresholds, this defines the threshold. For integer values (e.g. Temperature), the value is the threshold. For scientific values (e.g. BER levels), the value is the negative exponent. For example, to set a BER threshold of 10^-3, the value set here should be +3.

mnPrAlarmConfSet.name: mnPrAlarmConfSet
mnPrAlarmConfSet.description: True if the alarm is currently active, false otherwise.

mnPrNMConfTable.name: mnPrNMConfTable
mnPrNMConfTable.description: A table containing network management configuration information for each radio within the link.

mnPrNMConfEntry.name: mnPrNMConfEntry
mnPrNMConfEntry.description: A set of network management configuration information for a single radio within the link.

mnPrNMConfDefGateway.name: mnPrNMConfDefGateway
mnPrNMConfDefGateway.description: This object configures the IPv4 address of the default gateway available via the ethernet interface for this radio.

mnPrNMConfTrapMode.name: mnPrNMConfTrapMode
mnPrNMConfTrapMode.description: Controls what traps are sent: silent: No traps sent terse: Only the Major and Minor summary traps are sent verbose: All traps are sent

mnPrNMConfTFTPAddr.name: mnPrNMConfTFTPAddr
mnPrNMConfTFTPAddr.description: This object configures the IPv4 address of the TFTP server.

mnPrNMConfTFTPFile.name: mnPrNMConfTFTPFile
mnPrNMConfTFTPFile.description: This object configures the default filename to use for TFTP transfers.

mnPrNMConfSNTPAddr.name: mnPrNMConfSNTPAddr
mnPrNMConfSNTPAddr.description: This object configures the IPv4 address of the SNTP server.

mnPrNMConfSNTPInterval.name: mnPrNMConfSNTPInterval
mnPrNMConfSNTPInterval.description: The interval in minutes between sucessive scheduled polls of the SNTP server.

mnPrNMConfSNTPTimeout.name: mnPrNMConfSNTPTimeout
mnPrNMConfSNTPTimeout.description: The number of seconds to wait before declaring that an SNTP request has timed out.

mnPrIPIfConfTable.name: mnPrIPIfConfTable
mnPrIPIfConfTable.description: A table that contains configuration information about each of the radio's IP interfaces.

mnPrIPIfConfEntry.name: mnPrIPIfConfEntry
mnPrIPIfConfEntry.description: Configuration information about one of the radio's IP interfaces.

mnIPIfIndex.name: mnIPIfIndex
mnIPIfIndex.description: The index for the IP Interfaces Table (these match the numbering used for these same interface in the MIB-II IfTable.)

mnPrIPIfConfIPAddr.name: mnPrIPIfConfIPAddr
mnPrIPIfConfIPAddr.description: The IP address for this interface.

mnPrIPIfConfSubnetMask.name: mnPrIPIfConfSubnetMask
mnPrIPIfConfSubnetMask.description: The subnet mask for this interface.

mnPrIPIfConfRouting.name: mnPrIPIfConfRouting
mnPrIPIfConfRouting.description: The routing protocol used on this interface.

mnPrIPIfConfRoutingBit.name: mnPrIPIfConfRoutingBit
mnPrIPIfConfRoutingBit.description: A bitmap providing more information for the selected routing type. For RIP, the LSB is set if a custom advisement is to be used.

mnPrIPIfConfCustomAddress.name: mnPrIPIfConfCustomAddress
mnPrIPIfConfCustomAddress.description: If custom advisement is enabled for RIP, this is the address that is sent out on RIP packets for this port.

mnPrIPIfConfCustomSubnet.name: mnPrIPIfConfCustomSubnet
mnPrIPIfConfCustomSubnet.description: If custom advisement is enabled for RIP, this is the subnet that is sent out on RIP packets for this port.

mnPrRouteConfTable.name: mnPrRouteConfTable
mnPrRouteConfTable.description: Static routing configuration for this radio.

mnPrRouteConfEntry.name: mnPrRouteConfEntry
mnPrRouteConfEntry.description: Configuration information for use in creating and maintaining static routes.

mnPrRouteConfIndex.name: mnPrRouteConfIndex
mnPrRouteConfIndex.description: The index of the static routing database that contains this row

mnPrRouteConfDest.name: mnPrRouteConfDest
mnPrRouteConfDest.description: The destination IP address of this route.

mnPrRouteConfMask.name: mnPrRouteConfMask
mnPrRouteConfMask.description: Indicate the mask to be logical-ANDed with the destination address before being compared to the value in the mnPrRouteConfDest field. For those systems that do not support arbitrary subnet masks, an agent constructs the value of the mnPrRouteConfMask by determining whether the value of the correspondent mnPrRouteConfDest field belong to a class-A, B, or C network, and then using one of: mask network 255.0.0.0 class-A 255.255.0.0 class-B 255.255.255.0 class-C

mnPrRouteConfNextHop.name: mnPrRouteConfNextHop
mnPrRouteConfNextHop.description: The IP address of the next hop of this route. (In the case of a route bound to an interface which is realized via a broadcast media, the value of this field is the agent's IP address on that interface.)

mnPrRouteConfMetric.name: mnPrRouteConfMetric
mnPrRouteConfMetric.description: The routing metric for this route.

mnPrRouteConfRowStatus.name: mnPrRouteConfRowStatus
mnPrRouteConfRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row in the mnPrRouteConfTable: active (1) notInService (2) notReady (3) (not setable) createAndGo (4) (can be set, but not supported by this table) createAndWait(5) destroy (6) A static route is not qualified for activation until instances of all columns of the current row have an appropriate value.

mnTrapIndex.name: mnTrapIndex
mnTrapIndex.description: The index of the trap destination configuration entry.

mnPrTrapConfTrapAddr.name: mnPrTrapConfTrapAddr
mnPrTrapConfTrapAddr.description: The IP address of the trap destination.

mnPrTrapConfTrapComm.name: mnPrTrapConfTrapComm
mnPrTrapConfTrapComm.description: The trap community string to use when sending to the associated trap trap destination.

mnPrTrapConfRowStatus.name: mnPrTrapConfRowStatus
mnPrTrapConfRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row in the mnPrTrapConfTable: active (1) notInService (2) notReady (3) (not setable) createAndGo (4) (can be set, but not supported by this table) createAndWait(5) destroy (6) A row is not qualified for activation until instances of all columns of the row have an appropriate value.

mnPrPPPConfTable.name: mnPrPPPConfTable
mnPrPPPConfTable.description: PPP Configuration Parameters for this radio.

mnPrPPPConfBaudRate.name: mnPrPPPConfBaudRate
mnPrPPPConfBaudRate.description: The baud rate for the external modem port.

mnPrPPPConfInitString.name: mnPrPPPConfInitString
mnPrPPPConfInitString.description: The initialization string for the external modem.

mnPrPPPConfChapUser.name: mnPrPPPConfChapUser
mnPrPPPConfChapUser.description: The initialization string for the external modem.

mnPrPPPConfChapSecret.name: mnPrPPPConfChapSecret
mnPrPPPConfChapSecret.description: The CHAP secret needed to access the external modem port.

mnPrPerfHistConfTable.name: mnPrPerfHistConfTable
mnPrPerfHistConfTable.description: Performance History Configuration Parameters for each radio.

mnPrPerfHistConfEnable.name: mnPrPerfHistConfEnable
mnPrPerfHistConfEnable.description: This object provides a means to administratively enable or disable the collection of Performance History data.

mnPrPerfHistConfInterval.name: mnPrPerfHistConfInterval
mnPrPerfHistConfInterval.description: The number of seconds between each Performance History sample.

mnPrPerfHistConfFilename.name: mnPrPerfHistConfFilename
mnPrPerfHistConfFilename.description: This object configures the filename to be used for manual uploads of Performance History in CSV format. It also serves as the basename for automatic scheduled uploads which will append the date and time to this filename just in front of the filetype extension if any.

mnPrPerfHistConfUploadInterval.name: mnPrPerfHistConfUploadInterval
mnPrPerfHistConfUploadInterval.description: The number of seconds to collect Performance History data before automatically uploading it in CSV format to the TFTP server. A value of 0 disables automatic uploads.

mnPrPerfHistConfVarTable.name: mnPrPerfHistConfVarTable
mnPrPerfHistConfVarTable.description: Performance History Variable Configuration Parameters for each radio.

mnPrPerfHistConfVarEntry.name: mnPrPerfHistConfVarEntry
mnPrPerfHistConfVarEntry.description: One Performance History Variable Configuration entry.

mnPrPerfHistConfVarName.name: mnPrPerfHistConfVarName
mnPrPerfHistConfVarName.description: This object displays the Performance History variable name for this record.

mnPrPerfHistConfVarEnable.name: mnPrPerfHistConfVarEnable
mnPrPerfHistConfVarEnable.description: This object provides a means to administratively enable or disable the collection of Performance History data for the selected performance variable.

mnPrTribE1ConfTable.name: mnPrTribE1ConfTable
mnPrTribE1ConfTable.description: A table containing configuration information about each E1/DS1 tributary within this link.

mnPrTribE1ConfEntry.name: mnPrTribE1ConfEntry
mnPrTribE1ConfEntry.description: A set of configuration information about a single E1/DS1 tributary within this link.

mnPrTribE1ConfLineType.name: mnPrTribE1ConfLineType
mnPrTribE1ConfLineType.description: This object provides a means to administratively configure the E1/DS1 line encoding state of this tributary. encodeHdb3B8zs(1) - Use HDB3 (E1) or B8ZS (DS1) line encoding for the specified tributary. encodeAmi(2) - Use AMI (E1 or DS1) line encoding for the specified tributary. Currently, all tributaries on a LIM are encoded as specified for the first tributary on that LIM (trib 1 for LIM A, trib 17 for LIM B). This will change in the future when the hardware is capable of per tributary encoding.

mnPrAuxConfTable.name: mnPrAuxConfTable
mnPrAuxConfTable.description: A table containing configuration parameters for the Auxiliary channels in the link

mnPrAuxConfEntry.name: mnPrAuxConfEntry
mnPrAuxConfEntry.description: A set of configuration parameters for a single Auxiliary channel within the link. Can be used to configure other similar ports in the Link, like the OW port in data mode.

mnPrAuxConfBaudRate.name: mnPrAuxConfBaudRate
mnPrAuxConfBaudRate.description: This object provides a means to configure the baud rate used for this auxiliary channel.

mnPrAuxConfParity.name: mnPrAuxConfParity
mnPrAuxConfParity.description: This object provides a means to configure the parity checking for this auxiliary channel.

mnPrAuxConfInversion.name: mnPrAuxConfInversion
mnPrAuxConfInversion.description: This object provides a means to configure the signal inversion for this auxiliary channel.

mnPrAuxConfStopBits.name: mnPrAuxConfStopBits
mnPrAuxConfStopBits.description: This object provides a means to configure the number of stop bits used for this auxiliary channel.

mnPrEthPortConfTable.name: mnPrEthPortConfTable
mnPrEthPortConfTable.description: A table containing configuration parameters for Ethernet ports in the link, particularly the auxilliary non-LIM ports.

mnPrEthPortConfEntry.name: mnPrEthPortConfEntry
mnPrEthPortConfEntry.description: A set of configuration parameters for a single Ethernet port within the link.

mnPrEthPortIndex.name: mnPrEthPortIndex
mnPrEthPortIndex.description: NMS Port Configuration Index: 1 = NMS 1 2 = NMS 2 3 = Integral Ethernet 1 4 = Integral Ethernet 2 Range potentially allows tributaries to be indexed.

mnPrEthPortConfSpeed.name: mnPrEthPortConfSpeed
mnPrEthPortConfSpeed.description: This object provides a means to configure the LAN speed settings for the Ethernet ports. It allows the user to enable auto-negotiation or set the speed and duplex settings to a fixed value.

mnPrSwitchPlaneConfTable.name: mnPrSwitchPlaneConfTable
mnPrSwitchPlaneConfTable.description: A table containing configuration parameters (and control and status variables) for the switching planes in the link. A protected link contains pairs of redundant components (generally in a primary and associated secondary SPU). The pair defines a switching plane. This table has a row for every redundant component in the link.

mnPrSwitchPlaneConfEntry.name: mnPrSwitchPlaneConfEntry
mnPrSwitchPlaneConfEntry.description: A set of configuration parameters for a single redundant component within the link.

mnPrSwitchPlaneIndex.name: mnPrSwitchPlaneIndex
mnPrSwitchPlaneIndex.description: Switch Configuration Index. 1 = TxMux 2 = TxMod 3 = RxDMux 4 = RxDMod etc. Range sized to allow tributaries to be indexed.

mnPrSCPCtlTable.name: mnPrSCPCtlTable
mnPrSCPCtlTable.description: A table that controls the System Command Processor for each radio in the link.

mnPrSCPCtlEntry.name: mnPrSCPCtlEntry
mnPrSCPCtlEntry.description: A set of System Command Processor control information for a single radio within the link.

mnPrSCPCtlCmd.name: mnPrSCPCtlCmd
mnPrSCPCtlCmd.description: The system command control object for this radio. Setting this object to a value other than `idle' (1) has the side effect of invoking the associated system command. When read, the value of this object provides an indication of the currently invoked system control command, if any. The value of this object returns to `idle' (1) when the invoked command has completed execution. Writing 'idle' to the object will cancel the command that is in progress. Whenever the value of this object is not `idle', attempts to write a value to this object other than 'idle' will return an error.

mnPrSCPCtlCmdStringArg.name: mnPrSCPCtlCmdStringArg
mnPrSCPCtlCmdStringArg.description: A string argument used by the System Command Processor. Can be used for a filename, for example.

mnPrSCPCtlCmdNumArg.name: mnPrSCPCtlCmdNumArg
mnPrSCPCtlCmdNumArg.description: A numeric argument used by the System Command Processor.

mnPrSCPCtlCmdProgress.name: mnPrSCPCtlCmdProgress
mnPrSCPCtlCmdProgress.description: This object provides an indication of the progress of the current system command. The value returned by this object is a percentage representing the approximate percentage of the estimated total command time that has elapsed. If the current value of the mnPrSCPCtlCmd object is `idle' the value of this object is zero(0).

mnPrSCPCtlCmdResult.name: mnPrSCPCtlCmdResult
mnPrSCPCtlCmdResult.description: The system control command result. The enumerated values are interpreted as follows: `inProgress' - The system command is still in progress. `success' - The system command completed successfully. `failure' - The system command did not complete, or completed with errors. `aborted' - The system command was cancelled by the user (by writing 'idle' to mnPrSCPCtlCmd).

mnPrVlanDeviceConfTable.name: mnPrVlanDeviceConfTable
mnPrVlanDeviceConfTable.description: A table containing configuration information about each VLAN-capable device within this link.

mnPrVlanDeviceConfEntry.name: mnPrVlanDeviceConfEntry
mnPrVlanDeviceConfEntry.description: A set of configuration information about a single Vlan device within this link.

mnPrVlanDeviceCapabilities.name: mnPrVlanDeviceCapabilities
mnPrVlanDeviceCapabilities.description: Indicates the optional parts of IEEE 802.1D and 802.1Q that are implemented by this device and are manageable through this MIB. Capabilities that are allowed on a per-port basis are indicated in mnPrPortCapabilities. This maps directly to dot1dDeviceCapabilities.

mnPrVlanDeviceTfcClsEnabled.name: mnPrVlanDeviceTfcClsEnabled
mnPrVlanDeviceTfcClsEnabled.description: The value true(1) indicates that Traffic Classes are enabled on this bridge. When false(2), the bridge operates with a single priority level for all traffic. Maps directly to dot1dTrafficClassesEnabled.

mnPrVlanDeviceNumTrafficClasses.name: mnPrVlanDeviceNumTrafficClasses
mnPrVlanDeviceNumTrafficClasses.description: The number of egress traffic classes supported on this device. This object may optionally be read-only. On this device, it is set to 4. Maps to dot1dPortNumTrafficClasses, but is reported per device instead of per port.

mnPrVlanTrafficClassOrder.name: mnPrVlanTrafficClassOrder
mnPrVlanTrafficClassOrder.description: When mnPrVlanDeviceTrafficClassesEnabled is true, this will tell the device in what order to look at incomming packets for sorting into traffic classes. For example, if option 1 is selected, the device will first look at the VLAN tag containing IEEE 802.1p information if present, else it will look at the IPv4 Type of Service field or the IPv6 Traffic Classes field if present, else it will use the default priority determined by mnPrVLANPortDefaultUserPriority. If option 5 is selected, the device will only look at the default priority for the port.

mnPrVlanTrafficClassWieghted.name: mnPrVlanTrafficClassWieghted
mnPrVlanTrafficClassWieghted.description: When mnPrVlanDeviceTrafficClassesEnabled is true, this will tell the device how to handle egressing packets based upon traffic class. When false(2), it will output all high priority packets before outputing any lower priority packets. When true(1), it will output based on an 8-4-2-1 packet wieghting scheme based upon traffic class.

mnPrVlanDeviceVlanVersionNumber.name: mnPrVlanDeviceVlanVersionNumber
mnPrVlanDeviceVlanVersionNumber.description: The version number of IEEE 802.1Q that this device supports. Maps directly to dot1qVlanVersionNumber.

mnPrVlanDeviceMaxVlanId.name: mnPrVlanDeviceMaxVlanId
mnPrVlanDeviceMaxVlanId.description: The maximum IEEE 802.1Q VLAN ID that this device supports. Maps directly to dot1qMaxVlanId.

mnPrVlanDeviceMaxSupportedVlans.name: mnPrVlanDeviceMaxSupportedVlans
mnPrVlanDeviceMaxSupportedVlans.description: The maximum number of IEEE 802.1Q VLANs that this device supports. Maps directly to dot1qMaxSupportedVlans

mnPrVlanDeviceNumVlans.name: mnPrVlanDeviceNumVlans
mnPrVlanDeviceNumVlans.description: The current number of IEEE 802.1Q VLANs that are configured in this device. Maps directly to dot1qNumVlans

mnPrVlanDeviceNumDeletes.name: mnPrVlanDeviceNumDeletes
mnPrVlanDeviceNumDeletes.description: The number of times a VLAN entry has been deleted from the mnPr1qVlanCurrentTable (for any reason). If an entry is deleted, then inserted, and then deleted, this counter will be incremented by 2. Maps directly to dot1qVlanNumDeletes.

mnPrVlanDeviceLinkLossForwarding.name: mnPrVlanDeviceLinkLossForwarding
mnPrVlanDeviceLinkLossForwarding.description: Determines how the device ports should behave when the microwave link is lost. If no_llf(1) is selected, then the device will continue to operate. If total_llf(2) is selected, then all ports on the device will be disabled. If link_port_only(3) is selected, then data will no longer be sent to the link port, but the other ports will remain active. This is useful if you are switching data locally. totalLlfFeLos(4) is like totalLlf(2), but also acts if the far end LIM sees a LOS (if all ports are in LOS state).

mnPrVlanDevice1qEnabled.name: mnPrVlanDevice1qEnabled
mnPrVlanDevice1qEnabled.description: Enables the device for 802.1Q VLANS. If it is false(2), the device operates as a simple transperant bridge.

mnPrVlanDeviceIgnoreTags.name: mnPrVlanDeviceIgnoreTags
mnPrVlanDeviceIgnoreTags.description: Tells the device to ignore any incoming tags. All tags will have the default VLAN-Id for its ingress port associcated with it. The original tag will be kept in tact, and a second tag will be added.

mnPrVlanPortConfTable.name: mnPrVlanPortConfTable
mnPrVlanPortConfTable.description: A table containing configuration information about each VLAN-capable port within this link.

mnPrVlanPortConfEntry.name: mnPrVlanPortConfEntry
mnPrVlanPortConfEntry.description: A set of configuration information about a single VLAN port within this link.

mnPrVlanPortCapabilities.name: mnPrVlanPortCapabilities
mnPrVlanPortCapabilities.description: Indicates the parts of IEEE 802.1D and 802.1Q that are optional on a per-port basis that are implemented by this device and are manageable through this MIB. Maps directly to dot1dPortCapabilities.

mnPrVlanPortDefaultUserPriority.name: mnPrVlanPortDefaultUserPriority
mnPrVlanPortDefaultUserPriority.description: The default ingress User Priority for this port. This only has effect on media, such as Ethernet, that do not support native User Priority. Maps directly to dot1dPortDefaultUserPriority

mnPrVlanPortPvid.name: mnPrVlanPortPvid
mnPrVlanPortPvid.description: The PVID, the VLAN ID assigned to untagged frames or Priority-Tagged frames received on this port. Maps directly to dot1qPvid.

mnPrVlanPortAcceptableFrameTypes.name: mnPrVlanPortAcceptableFrameTypes
mnPrVlanPortAcceptableFrameTypes.description: When this is admitOnlyVlanTagged(2) the device will discard untagged frames or Priority-Tagged frames received on this port. When admitAll(1), untagged frames or Priority-Tagged frames received on this port will be accepted and assigned to the PVID for this port. This control does not affect VLAN independent BPDU frames, such as GVRP and STP. It does affect VLAN dependent BPDU frames, such as GMRP. On Proteus AMT, this can only be set to admitAll(1). Maps directly to dot1qPortAcceptableFrameTypes.

mnPrVlanPortIngressFiltering.name: mnPrVlanPortIngressFiltering
mnPrVlanPortIngressFiltering.description: When this is true(1) the device will discard incoming frames for VLANs which do not include this Port in its Member set. When false(2), the port will accept all incoming frames. This control does not affect VLAN independent BPDU frames, such as GVRP and STP. It does affect VLAN dependent BPDU frames, such as GMRP. Maps directly to dot1qPortIngressFiltering

mnPrVlanPortGvrpStatus.name: mnPrVlanPortGvrpStatus
mnPrVlanPortGvrpStatus.description: The state of GVRP operation on this port. The value true(1) indicates that GVRP is enabled on this port, as long as dot1qGvrpStatus is also enabled for this device. When false(2) but dot1qGvrpStatus is still enabled for the device, GVRP is disabled on this port: any GVRP packets received will be silently discarded and no GVRP registrations will be propagated from other ports. This object affects all GVRP Applicant and Registrar state machines on this port. A transition from false(2) to true(1) will cause a reset of all GVRP state machines on this port. On Proteus AMT, this is always false(2).

mnPrVlanPortLineSpeed.name: mnPrVlanPortLineSpeed
mnPrVlanPortLineSpeed.description: The speed of this port. It can either Auto-negotiate with the link partner (1), be set to half-duplex 10 BaseT(2), half-duplex 100 BaseT(3), or full-duplex 100 BaseT(4).

mnPrVlanPortRateLimitPri0.name: mnPrVlanPortRateLimitPri0
mnPrVlanPortRateLimitPri0.description: The ingress rate limit for priority 0 frames on this port. Note that the valid values are 100 Mbps (no limiting), 128 kbps, 256 kbps, 512 kbps, 1 mbps, 2 mbps, 4 mbps, or 8 mbps are the only valid values. 16, 32, and 64 mbps are not available for priority 0 packets.

mnPrVlanPortRateLimitPri1.name: mnPrVlanPortRateLimitPri1
mnPrVlanPortRateLimitPri1.description: The rate limit for priority 1 frames on this port. Note that the valid values are either the same value as priority 0 packets or twice the value of priority 0 packets. All other set attempts will be rejected. Also, this value will change if mnPrVlanPortRateLimitPri0 changes.

mnPrVlanPortRateLimitPri2.name: mnPrVlanPortRateLimitPri2
mnPrVlanPortRateLimitPri2.description: The rate limit for priority 2 frames on this port. Note that the valid values are either the same value as priority 1 packets or twice the value of priority 1 packets. All other set attempts will be rejected. Also, this value will change if mnPrVlanPortRateLimitPri1 changes.

mnPrVlanPortRateLimitPri3.name: mnPrVlanPortRateLimitPri3
mnPrVlanPortRateLimitPri3.description: The rate limit for priority 3 frames on this port. Note that the valid values are either the same value as priority 2 packets or twice the value of priority 2 packets. All other set attempts will be rejected. Also, this value will change if mnPrVlanPortRateLimitPri2 changes.

mnPr1qVlanCurrentTable.name: mnPr1qVlanCurrentTable
mnPr1qVlanCurrentTable.description: A table containing current configuration information for each VLAN currently configured into the device by (local or network) management, or dynamically created as a result of GVRP requests received. Maps directly to dot1qVlanCurrentTable.

mnPr1qVlanCurrentEntry.name: mnPr1qVlanCurrentEntry
mnPr1qVlanCurrentEntry.description: Information for a VLAN configured into the device by (local or network) management, or dynamically created as a result of GVRP requests received. Maps directly to dot1qVlanCurrentEntry, but is indexed on a (1..64) basis instead of VlanId

mnPr1qVlanIndex.name: mnPr1qVlanIndex
mnPr1qVlanIndex.description: The identifier refering to this VLAN. Maps directly to dot1qVlanIndex, but is not equivalent to the VLAN-ID.

mnPr1qVlanId.name: mnPr1qVlanId
mnPr1qVlanId.description: The VLAN-ID associated with this VLAN.

mnPr1qVlanFdbId.name: mnPr1qVlanFdbId
mnPr1qVlanFdbId.description: The Filtering Database used by this VLAN. This is one of the dot1qFdbId values in the dot1qFdbTable. This value is allocated automatically by the device whenever the VLAN is created: either dynamically by GVRP, or by management, in dot1qVlanStaticTable. Allocation of this value follows the learning constraints defined for this VLAN in dot1qLearningConstraintsTable. Since ther is only one filtering database on Proteus AMT, this value will always be 1. Maps directly to dot1qVlanFdbId.

mnPr1qVlanCurrentEgressPorts.name: mnPr1qVlanCurrentEgressPorts
mnPr1qVlanCurrentEgressPorts.description: The set of ports which are transmitting traffic for this VLAN as either tagged or untagged frames. Maps directly to dot1qVlanCurrentEgressPorts.

mnPr1qVlanCurrentUntaggedPorts.name: mnPr1qVlanCurrentUntaggedPorts
mnPr1qVlanCurrentUntaggedPorts.description: The set of ports which are transmitting traffic for this VLAN as untagged frames. Maps directly to dot1qVlanCurrentUntaggedPorts.

mnPr1qVlanStatus.name: mnPr1qVlanStatus
mnPr1qVlanStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so differ from the following values. permanent(2) - this entry, corresponding to an entry in dot1qVlanStaticTable, is currently in use and will remain so after the next reset of the device. The port lists for this entry include ports from the equivalent dot1qVlanStaticTable entry and ports learnt dynamically. dynamicGvrp(3) - this entry is currently in use and will remain so until removed by GVRP. There is no static entry for this VLAN and it will be removed when the last port leaves the VLAN. Maps directly to dot1qVlanStatus.

mnPr1qVlanCreationTime.name: mnPr1qVlanCreationTime
mnPr1qVlanCreationTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when this VLAN was created. Maps directly to dot1qVlanCreationTime.

mnPr1qVlanStaticTable.name: mnPr1qVlanStaticTable
